author: wrowe
msg: Include the missing mod_cache, mod_disk_cache, mod_mem_cache, bring in
the manual/style/ directory and add back header/footer.html since we will
be allowing folks to regenerate docs from .xml, apparently.  All based on
my comparisons with binbuild/unix.
We still don't have source, but that's really becoming pretty irrelevant
given the size of these new binbuilds [and I thought the win32 installer
.msi's were getting bloated.]

author: wrowe
msg: Fix the failure to install as-service bug - the trailing backslash
[always present in MSI installer paths] horks Apache2.0 in a way that
never bothered 1.3.  Simply add a trailing period following that slash.

author: wrowe
msg: Replace HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\CurrentVersion\Run ... with
the corresponding StartUp group shortcut to ApacheMonitor,
so the user has more control, and we eliminate our 'destroyed
the Run key' bug.
Also grab ab/abs [w/o or w/ SSL] from the build tree since we can't
distingush which 'target\bin\ab.exe' was copied.
Finally, bumps for .35 - horah!
